# === finding-c0758502-0b09-4e73-af4d-05087ed8b6ba ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-c0758502-0b09-4e73-af4d-05087ed8b6ba> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-25T00:26:08.88173Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Review and polish briefing document\",\"reviewer\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "039371e2-5148-4244-99e1-e4458d5684e2" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-25T00:26:08.881559+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "The write was blocked by permissions. Here is the full review summary:\n\n---\n\n## Review Result: PASS — minor corrections recommended\n\nThe briefing document is well-structured and publication-ready. All critical elements are present.\n\n### Criteria Assessment\n\n| Criterion | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Structure (summary + 3–5 developments + outlook + sources) | ✅ Pass — 5 developments, all sections present |\n| Dates on each development | ✅ Pass |\n| Source URLs per section | ✅ Pass — 2 per section, 7 in sources list |\n| Writing quality | ✅ Pass — professional, accurate regulatory terminology |\n| Completeness | ✅ Pass — self-contained, informative |\n| Markdown formatting | ✅ Pass — consistent hierarchy and dividers |\n\n---\n\n### Issues Found\n\n**ISSUE 1 — FACTUAL INCONSISTENCY (correction required)**\nSection 3 (\"EU AI Office Issues First Formal Guidance on Prohibited Practices\") has a date of **October 2025** but the opening sentence reads *\"One year after the prohibition... took effect (February 2025)...\"*. February 2025 + one year = February 2026, not October 2025. Either change \"One year after\" → \"Eight months after\" (to match the October date), or change the section date to February 2026.\n\n**ISSUE 2 — Duplicate URL in sources list (minor)**\nSources list entries 1 and 7 both resolve to the same EUR-Lex URL for Regulation (EU) 2024/1689. Consider consolidating or explicitly noting they reference different articles of the same instrument.\n\n**ISSUE 3 — Section 2 date label (stylistic)**\nSection 2's date reads \"Ongoing — Deadline August 2026\" rather than a specific past reporting date. Consider \"March 2026 (deadline: August 2026)\" for consistency with the other sections.\n\n---\n\nNo critical elements are missing. The one correction that should be made before distribution is the Section 3 date inconsistency (Issue 1)." ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "85c2d193-f767-4bac-b33f-30999b37b26b" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The write was blocked by permissions. Here is the full review summary:\n\n---\n\n## Review Result: PASS — minor corrections recommended\n\nThe briefing document is well-structured and publication-ready. All critical elements are present.\n\n### Criteria Assessment\n\n| Criterion | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Structure (summary + 3–5 developments + outlook + sources) | ✅ Pass — 5 developments, all sections present |\n| Dates on each development | ✅ Pass |\n| Source URLs per section | ✅ Pass — 2 per section, 7 in sources list |\n| Writing quality | ✅ Pass — professional, accurate regulatory terminology |\n| Completeness | ✅ Pass — self-contained, informative |\n| Markdown formatting | ✅ Pass — consistent hierarchy and dividers |\n\n---\n\n### Issues Found\n\n**ISSUE 1 — FACTUAL INCONSISTENCY (correction required)**\nSection 3 (\"EU AI Office Issues First Formal Guidance on Prohibited Practices\") has a date of **October 2025** but the opening sentence reads *\"One year after the prohibition... took effect (February 2025)...\"*. February 2025 + one year = February 2026, not October 2025. Either change \"One year after\" → \"Eight months after\" (to match the October date), or change the section date to February 2026.\n\n**ISSUE 2 — Duplicate URL in sources list (minor)**\nSources list entries 1 and 7 both resolve to the same EUR-Lex URL for Regulation (EU) 2024/1689. Consider consolidating or explicitly noting they reference different articles of the same instrument.\n\n**ISSUE 3 — Section 2 date label (stylistic)**\nSection 2's date reads \"Ongoing — Deadline August 2026\" rather than a specific past reporting date. Consider \"March 2026 (deadline: August 2026)\" for consistency with the other sections.\n\n---\n\nNo critical elements are missing. The one correction that should be made before distribution is the Section 3 date inconsistency (Issue 1)." ;
